<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-17T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="93" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4626: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Personal Representative of the President</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-17T14:00:00-05:00">January 17, 1934—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>36. Batista has just sent me word that in view of the very precarious
                            strike situation (seriously endangering enormous American properties)
                            provoked by Guiteras and also in view of Hevia’s inability to secure the
                            full support of Mendieta group he has decided to declare Mendieta
                            President this afternoon. He may meet with armed resistance from the
                            Cuban Navy.</p>
                        <p>I do not know that this decision is final but he says now that he has
                            decided.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>